org.youscope.common.table

Interface TableProducerConfiguration

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutoFocusJobConfiguration, CellDetectionConfiguration, CellDetectionJobConfiguration, CellXConfiguration, ControllerJobConfiguration, DropletMicrofluidicJobConfiguration, FluigentJobConfiguration, NemesysJobConfiguration, QuickDetectConfiguration, StatisticsJobConfiguration

    public interface TableProducerConfiguration
    Interface each measurement component configuration should implement if its corresponding component produces table data. By implementing this interface one accepts the contract that each component created as an artifact of this configuration also implements TableProducer, returning the same information as returned here.
    Author:
    Moritz Lang

    • Method Detail

      • getProducedTableDefinition

        TableDefinition getProducedTableDefinition()
        Returns the definition of the table layout of the tables produced by this producer, e.g. the number and types of its columns. This function should return the same TableDefinition as is returned by a measurement component created by this configuration, see TableProducer.getProducedTableDefinition().
        Returns:
        Information about of the produced tables.
